The analyses described in Sects. 3, 4, 5, and 6 are based on analysis of neutrino beam data at both the ND and FD. The DUNE neutrino beam is produced using protons from Fermilab’s Main Injector and a traditional horn-focusing system [5]. The polarity of the focusing magnets may be reversed to produce a neutrino- or antineutrino-dominated beam. This optimized beam configuration includes a three-horn focusing system with a 1 m long target embedded within the first horn and a decay pipe with 194m\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
