				\begin{document}$$\nu _\mu N \rightarrow \mu \pi N^\prime $$\end{document}, as muon and pion tracks can be easily confused in LArTPC detectors. The discrimination power of the DUNE ND LArTPC was evaluated using large simulated data sets of signal and background. Each simulated event represents a different neutrino-argon interaction in the active volume of the detector. Signal events were generated using a standalone code [148] that simulates trident production of muons and electrons through the scattering of νμ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
