				\begin{document}$$Z'$$\end{document} masses of O(few MeV) and below, strong constraints from measurements of the effective number of relativistic degrees of freedom during Big Bang Nucleosynthesis (BBN) apply [165, 166]. Taking into account all relevant constraints, parameter space to explain (g-2)μ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
