				\begin{document}$$n-{\bar{n}}$$\end{document} annihilation events is caused by atmospheric neutrinos. As with nucleon decay, nuclear effects and FSI make the picture more complicated. As shown in Table  9, every decay mode contains at least one charged pion and one neutral pion. The pion FSI in the hA2015 model in GENIE include pion elastic and inelastic scattering, charge exchange and absorption.Table 9
