DUNE’s large FD LArTPC modules provide an excellent setting to conduct searches for neutrinos arising from DM annihilation in the core of the sun. These would typically result in a high-energy neutrino signal almost always accompanied by a low-energy neutrino component, which has its origin in a hadronic cascade that develops in the dense solar medium and produces large numbers of light long-lived mesons, such as π+\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
